{{Expand|time=2015-08-18T12:31:56+00:00}}
{{恐怖主義}}{{战争}}
'''自殺攻擊'''或称'''自杀式袭击'''、'''人肉炸彈'''，是一種將[[自杀|自杀]]擴大為傷害自己及目標者的行為，現代的自殺式攻擊通常是由自殺者在身上綁好[[炸彈|炸彈]]，走到目標地，或是以裝滿炸彈的車衝撞特定目標然後進行引爆，以達到傷害和宣傳信念的手段。自杀攻击在历史上屡见不鲜，在军事冲突有诸如[[特別攻擊隊|神风特攻队]]这样的例子，而在[[恐怖主义|恐怖主义]]中最著名的案例则是[[九一一袭击事件|911事件]]。

从第二次世界大战结束到1980年间，世界上任何地方实施成功的自杀式袭击都非常少，<ref name="Kay-2005">{{cite news|last1=Kay|first1=Jonathan|title=Dying to Win: The Strategic Logic of Suicide Terrorism|url=http://www.islamdaily.org/en/wahabism/3463.dying-to-win-the-strategic-logic-of-suicide-terror.htm|access-date=5 October 2015|work=Islam Daily|date=13 September 2005}}</ref> 但从1981年到2015年9月，40多个国家共发生了4814起自杀式袭击，造成45000多人死亡。<ref name="CPoST">{{cite web|title=Chicago Project on Security and Terrorism. Suicide Attack Database|url=http://cpostdata.uchicago.edu/search_new.php?clear=1|access-date=24 March 2016|website=Cpostdata.uchicago.edu|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160124204240/http://cpostdata.uchicago.edu/search_new.php?clear=1|archive-date=24 January 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> 在此期间，全球此类自杀式袭击的发生率从1980年代的平均每年3起逐步增加到1990年的每月1起，<ref name="Atran_128">{{cite web|title=The Moral Logic and Growth of Suicide Terrorism (figure 1, pg. 128)|url=http://www.sitemaker.umich.edu/satran/files/twq06spring_atran.pdf#2|access-date=July 11, 2015|last=Atran|first=Scott|website=sitemaker.umich.edu|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150623022648/http://www.sitemaker.umich.edu/satran/files/twq06spring_atran.pdf|archive-date=June 23, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> 而从2001年至2003年的每周1起则又逐步增加到2003年至2015年间每天1起。<ref name="CPoST" />

自杀式袭击往往比其他恐怖袭击更加致命却具有{{Internal link helper/en|破坏性|List of terrorist incidents}}，<ref name="Hoffman-6-2003">{{cite journal|title=The Logic of Suicide Terrorism|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/magazine/archive/2003/06/the-logic-of-suicide-terrorism/302739/|last=Hoffman|first=Bruce|date=June 2003|journal=The Atlantic|quote=According to data from the Rand Corporation's chronology of international terrorism incidents, suicide attacks on average kill four times as many people as other terrorist acts.|access-date=4 October 2015}}</ref>因为这种袭击方式能让实施者隐藏袭击武器，并在最终引爆才会被人发现，而且自杀式袭击并不依赖远程遥控、延迟爆炸、制定逃跑计划或呼叫救援这些方式。<ref name="Hoffman-6-2003" />在1981年至2006年期间，自杀式袭击仅占全世界所有恐怖袭击的4%，但造成的死亡人数却占所有与恐怖主义有关的死亡人数的32% (14599人)。而90%的自杀式袭击发生在[[阿富汗|阿富汗]]、[[伊拉克|伊拉克]]、[[以色列|以色列]]、[[巴勒斯坦领土|巴勒斯坦领土]]、[[巴基斯坦|巴基斯坦]]和[[斯里蘭卡|斯里兰卡]]。<ref name="what">{{cite web|title=What Motivates the Suicide Bombers?|url=http://yaleglobal.yale.edu/content/what-motivates-suicide-bombers-0|access-date=November 2, 2012|date=September 3, 2009|last=Hassan|first=Riaz|work=YaleGlobal|publisher=Yale Center for the Study of Globalization|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004215906/http://yaleglobal.yale.edu/content/what-motivates-suicide-bombers-0|archive-date=October 4, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>截至2015年，约四分之三的自杀式袭击都发生在阿富汗、巴基斯坦和伊拉克这三个国家。<ref name="CPOST-LOC-total">(Click "Search Database", then under "filter by", click "location". Afghanistan (1059) Iraq (1938) and Pakistan (490) have a total 3487 attacks out of a total of 4620 worldwide.){{cite web|title=Year: 1982–2015. Group|url=http://cpostdata.uchicago.edu/search_new.php?clear=1|access-date=2015-11-20|website=Chicago Project on Security and Terrorism Suicide Attack Database|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160124204240/http://cpostdata.uchicago.edu/search_new.php?clear=1|archive-date=2016-01-24|url-status=dead}}</ref>

自杀式袭击也会被作为一种[[心理战|心理战]]武器，目的是向目标人群灌输[[恐惧|恐惧氛围]]，<ref>{{cite journal|title=The systemic roots of suicide bombing|last=Hutchinson|first=W.|date=March 2007|journal=Systems Research and Behavioral Science|issue=2|doi=10.1002/sres.824|volume=24|pages=191–200}}</ref> <ref name="ict-dlci">{{cite web|title=The Social Psychology of Suicide Terrorism|url=http://www.ict.org.il/Article/1233/The-Social-Psychology-of-Suicide-Terrorism|access-date=22 December 2015|date=19 October 2014|website=ict.org.il|publisher=International Institute for Counter Terrorism|quote=Terrorism involves the use of force or violence in order to instill fear as a means of coercing individuals or groups to change their political or social positions which means that social influence is the ultimate goal of terrorism. Obviously we could say the same about suicide terrorism. [...] An alternative perspective views terrorism, including suicide terrorism, as tool: a means to an end and a tactic of warfare that anyone could use.|last1=de la Corte Ibáñez|first1=Luis}}</ref>瓦解“社会团结稳定安全”的结构和消除公众对[[公共领域|公共区域]]的安全感，也能表明实施者为实现其目标将不惜一切代价。<ref name="Hoffman-6-2003" />

自杀式袭击可能有多种动机。神风特攻队飞行员是完全服从军事命令下行动的，而其他自杀式袭击则是出于[[宗教|宗教]]或[[民族主義|民族主义]]目的。据分析师{{Internal link helper/en|罗伯特 · 佩普|Robert Pape}}说，在2003年之前，大多数自杀式袭击的目标都是[[军事占领|占领军]]部队。<ref>For example, 90% of attacks in Iraq prior to the [[Iraqi_conflict_(2003–present)|civil war]] (starting in 2003) aimed at forcing out occupying forces. Pape's tabulation of suicide attacks runs from 1980 to early 2004 in [[Dying_to_Win:_The_Strategic_Logic_of_Suicide_Terrorism|''Dying to Win'']] and to 2009 in [[Robert_Pape#Cutting_the_Fuse|''Cutting the Fuse'']].</ref>人类学家{{Internal link helper/en|斯科特 · 阿特兰|Scott Atran}}指出，自2004年以来，伊斯兰的[[殉教|殉道意识]]激励了绝大多数的自杀袭击者。<ref name="Atran_131_133">[http://www.sitemaker.umich.edu/satran/files/twq06spring_atran.pdf#5 Scott Atran| The Moral Logic and Growth of Suicide Terrorism] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150623022648/http://www.sitemaker.umich.edu/satran/files/twq06spring_atran.pdf#5|date=June 23, 2015}} (pp. 131, 133); sitemaker.umich.edu; accessed July 11, 2015.</ref>

== 定义 ==

==== 恐怖主义 ====
自杀式袭击包括以恐怖活动形式的自杀式袭击（通常被定义为“以恐吓为主要目的”或“意图造成平民或非战斗人员死亡或严重肢体伤害“的行动) ，也包括不针对非战斗人员的自杀式袭击。<ref>Definition given by [[Kofi_Annan|Kofi Annan]], March 2005 in the UN General Assembly, while Secretary General of the UN.{{cite web|title=Story: UN reform|url=https://www.un.org/unifeed/script.asp?scriptId=73|access-date=2010-02-24|publisher=United Nations|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070427012107/http://www.un.org/unifeed/script.asp?scriptId=73|archive-date=2007-04-27}}</ref>一名曾在伊斯兰激进分子中生活过的记者{{Internal link helper/en|杰森 · 伯克|Jason Burke}}提出了另一个定义，他认为大多数人还将恐怖主义定义为“使用或威胁使用严重暴力”来推进某种“事业”，并强调恐怖主义只是一种推进其“事业”的手段策略。<ref>{{cite book|author=Jason Burke|title=Al-Qaeda: The True Story of Radical Islam|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-_FJFFrit8AC|access-date=August 19, 2012|year=2004|publisher=I.B.Tauris|isbn=978-1-85043-666-9|pages=1–24 (22)}}</ref>  学者{{Internal link helper/en|弗雷德 · 哈利迪|Fred Halliday}}曾写道，将“恐怖分子“或者“恐怖主义”这两个称谓来赋予一个群体的行为也是一种策略，而恰好一些国家或者政府就会使用这种策略来否认反对派或者异议组织的“合法性“。<ref>F. Halliday. (2002). ''Two Hours that Shook the World: September 11, 2001 – Causes and Consequences'', Saqi; {{ISBN|0-86356-382-1}}, pp. 70–71</ref>

==== 自杀式恐怖主义 ====
[[File:Suicide-attacks-cpost-bigger-font.JPG|右]]
对于“自杀”的定义则是另外一个需要主要的问题。受政府聘用的教授艾米 · 佩达祖尔将自杀式恐怖主义本身定义为”意识到活着回来的几率几乎为零的人所犯下的暴力行为”，<ref>Pedahzur, p. 8</ref> 这里包括了有自杀式的攻击行为（如[[盧德國際機場掃射事件|卢德国际机场扫射事件]]或战场上的[[萬歲衝鋒|自杀冲锋]]），<ref name="ICT-STDC">{{cite web|title=Suicide Terrorism: Development and Characteristics|url=http://www.ict.org.il/Articles/tabid/66/Articlsid/42/Default.aspx|access-date=March 22, 2015|author=Yoram Schweitzer|date=April 21, 2000|publisher=[[International_Institute_for_Counter-Terrorism|International Institute for Counter-Terrorism]]|quote=... a very specific kind of attack. It does not deal with the very high-risk terror operations that leave only little chance of survival to their perpetrators. Such attacks as the Japanese Red Army's (JRA) attack at Lod airport in 1972, Abu Nidal's attack on a synagogue in Istanbul in 1986 and the PFLP-GC hand-glider attack on an army barracks in Kiryat Shmona in 1987 fall outside the scope of this paper. Also excluded were the self-inflicted deaths of members of terrorist organization, ... a politically motivated violent attack perpetrated by a self-aware individual (or individuals) who actively and purposely causes his own death through blowing himself up along with his chosen target. ... the perpetrator's ensured death is a precondition for the success of his mission."|author-link=Yoram Schweitzer}}</ref><ref name="Dodd">{{cite book|last1=Dodd|first1=Henry|title=A short history of suicide bombing|date=23 Aug 2013|publisher=Action on Armed Violence|url=https://aoav.org.uk/2013/a-short-history-of-suicide-bombings/|access-date=6 October 2015|quote=First of all let's be clear what kind of attacks we are talking about.  Suicide bombings are those that involve the deliberate death of the perpetrator. We’re not just talking about a reckless charge in battle. The focus is on those attacks where the perpetrator functions as a sophisticated guidance system for the weapon. They function as part human and part weapon. In this way they are suicide attacks rather than suicidal attacks.}}</ref>如果只关注真正意义上的“自杀袭击”，那对于其生存几率应该不是“接近于零”，而是等于零，因为"实施者要求任务成功的所需前提是必须确保自己能够死亡。"。<ref name="ICT-STDC" />{{自杀}}

